          "explanation": "(a) Excessive formation of crust(Ref. Cummings, 6th ed., 695)The excessive crusting leads to nasal obstruction in spite of roomy cavities.On removal of crusts there is bleeding. But there is no synechiae formation. There is no polypoidal change .",
