          "explanation": "Nasolacrimal duct is q membranous passage which begins at the lower end of the lacrimal sac. It runs downward,backward and laterally and opens in the inferior meatus of the nose. A fold of mucous membrane called the valve of Hasner forms an imperfect value at the lower end of the duct. Ref: Dhingra 6/e,135.",
          "hint": "Topic: Nose and paranasal sinuses"
