          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Ans. is 'a' i.e. Fossa of Rosenmuller Nasopharyngeal Ca:MC type is * - Squamous cell CaLymph node involvement is very common. Sometimes a cervical node may be the only manifestation of nasopharyngeal cancer (occult primary)Treatment of choice - Radiotherapy *",
