          "explanation": "Jarjaway' fracture of nasal septum occurs due to blows from the front. Fracture line stas just above the anterior nasal spine and runs horizontally backwards just above the junction of septal cailage with the vomer. Ref: Textbook of ENT; PL Dhingra;7th edition, pg no.165",
