          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Tuning fork test can be performed using tuning fork of different frequencies such as:\n. • MC used/ ideal for routine clinical practice is of 512 Hz.\n• Tuning fork of lower frequencies produce sense of bone vibration while those of higher frequencies have a shorter decay time and are thus not routinely preferred.\n• Tests done with tuning fork:\n■ Rinne’s test\n■ Weber's test\n■ Absolute bone conduction (ABC) test\n■ Bing test\n■ Gelle’s test\n■ Lewis test"
