          "explanation": "(c) Malignant Otitis externa(Ref. Cummings, 6th ed., 2618)Among the given options Malignant Otitis externa is locally invasive infective condition and leads to facial nerve palsy. It is seen in immunocompromised patients and is caused most commonly by pseudomonas.",
