          "explanation": "(c) b2 agonists(Ref. Scott Brown, Vol 2; 288)b2 agonists (salbutamol/terbutaline) have no role in respiratory obstruction due to adenoids. They are used in lower airway obstruction diseases, e.g. asthma, etc.",
          "hint": "Topic: Nose and PNS"
