          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Meniere's disease also called endolymphatic hydrops is a disorder of the inner ear where the endolymphatic system is distended with endolymph. It is characterized by Veigo Sensorineural hearing loss Tinnitus Aural fullness Veigo is due to K+ entry into perilymph and Causes irritation and is episodic Some cases of Meniere's disease show tullio phenomenon. SNHL is due to ion gradient imbalance.",
