          "explanation": "In laryngomalacia direct laryngoscopy shows elongated epiglottis, curled upon itself (omega-shaped), floppy aryepiglottic folds and prominent arytenoids. Pediatric Epiglottis is omega-shaped and arytenoids relatively large covering significant poion of the posterior glottis."
