          "explanation": "Ans: c (2 KHz) Ref: Dhingra, 3rd ed, p. 115 & p. 87Dip in bone conduction in otosclerosis & maximum occurs at 2000 Hz called Carhart notchDip Disappears after successful stapedectomy2 KHz dip - Otosclerosis4 KHz dip - Noise induced hearing loss8 KHz dip - Senile otosclerosis",
