          "explanation": "TREATMENT OF COMPLETE LARYNGEAL PALSY: Tracheostomy Gastrostomy Epiglottopexy Vocal cord plication Total laryngectomy Diversion procedures-Laryngotracheal separation, Laryngeal closure& permanent tracheostome Bilateral medialization i.e. Type I thyroplasty for aspiration requires adduction of the entirevocal cord. The technique works in carefully selectedcases of mild aspiration as it does not prevent all aspiration and risks patients requiring a tracheostomy,",
