          "explanation": "(c) FESS(Ref. Cummings, 6th ed., 760)The NCCT nose and PNS axial view shows the right maxillary sinus filled with mass, going to the nasal cavity and extending into the nasopharynx, suggestive of antrochoanal polyp. Also notice the crescent of air in the nasopharynx, between the mass and the posterior pharyngeal wall known as Dodd/ crescent sign.",
          "hint": "Topic: Nasal Polyposis"
