          "explanation": "Ans. is 'c' i.e., Little's area o Epistaxis is relatively common in children.o The most common cause of epistaxis is the mucosal maceration caused by upper respiratory infection and nose picking (trauma).o The usual site of bleeding is the anterior nasal septum, i.e.. Kiesselbach 's area (little's area)\"Most common cause of epistaxis in chidren is nose picking in the little's area \" -- Pediatric emergency.",
