          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "SNHL can be: a. Cochlear SNHL b. Retrocochlear SNHL Acoustic neuroma cause retrocochlear type of SNHL as it damages Vint' nerve. Meniere's disease causes cochlear deafness Impoant features of Retro Cochlear hearing loss /Acoustic Neuroma: Sensorineural hearing loss more marked in high frequencies. - Poor discrimination score (0-30%). - Recruitment phenomenon absent and roll over phenomenon present i.e. discrimination score fuher decreases when loudness is increased beyond a paicular point. - Sho increment sensitivity index (SISI) test will show a score of 0-20% in 70-90% cases. - Tone decay significant"
