          "explanation": "Nasopharyngeal carcinoma is most common in China paicularly in southern states and Taiwan. Factors operative in China are burning of incense or wood(polycyclic hydrocarbon), use of preserved salted fish (nitrosamines) along with vitamin C deficient diet. Infection with Epstein Barr Virus also act as predisposing factor."
