          "correctOptionId": "opt-3",
          "explanation": "Once the diagnosis has been made, treatment of the exact cause can be planned. When there is secondary infection with fever and toxaemia or purulent expectoration, antibiotics are the treatment of choice. Voice rest, avoidance of smoking and alcohol, Steam inhalation, Cough sedative, Analgesics, Steroids are the other treatment modalities. Ref: Textbook of diseases of ENT, PL Dhingra, 7th edition, pg no.328",
